title: Encyclopedia
description: Books giving information on many subjects or on many aspects of one subject and typically arranged alphabetically.

title: Telescope
description: A device used to observe distant objects by their emission, absorption, or reflection of electromagnetic radiation.

title: Aquarium
description: A vivarium of any size having at least one transparent side in which aquatic plants or animals are kept and displayed.

title: Hoverboard
description: A levitating board used for personal transportation.

title: Hourglass
description: An early device used to measure the passage of time.

title: Incandescent Lightbulb
description: An electric light with a wire filament heated until it glows.

title: Test
description: A means of finding out the nature, quality, or value of something.
